// Phase 5/6 perks catalog (Sims-style aspiration rewards). Players spend
// Ambition Points (AP) earned from any ambition's stage payoffs on perks
// drawn from this universal catalog.
//
// Schema (validated in perks.ts):
//   id          — stable string key
//   nameZh      — zh-CN player-facing name
//   descZh      — zh-CN one-paragraph blurb
//   apCost      — AP price; tier ladder is 1 AP / 2 AP / 4 AP
//   category    — vital | skill | social | economic | combat | faction
//   modifiers   — flat list of { statId, type, value } rows, same shape as
//                 backgrounds.json5. The sync layer folds these onto the
//                 character's StatSheet under `perk:<id>`. Perks whose
//                 downstream consumers don't ship yet leave modifiers
//                 empty.
//
// Modifier types: 'flat', 'percentAdd', 'percentMult', 'floor', 'cap'.
// Vital drain conventions: a "−10% hunger drain" perk is
// `{ statId: 'hungerDrainMul', type: 'percentMult', value: -0.10 }` since
// hungerDrainMul has base 1 and is multiplied into the per-tick drain.
// "All vitals" perks list each vital explicitly — there is no shorthand.
//
// Pricing intent: 1 AP = "small permanent quality-of-life nudge", 2 AP =
// "noticeable build choice", 4 AP = "significant lategame reward".

